   PARAMOUNT COMMUNICATIONS Co. (New York) -- Peter J. Boni
was named president of software and information services and
L. William Black was named president of business information
and publishing, two new divisions of Simon &amp; Schuster,
Paramount's book publishing subsidiary. Mr. Boni, 44 years
old, was previously president and chief operating officer for
On Line Software International Inc., Fort Lee, N.J. Mr.
Black, 44, previously was managing director for the U.S.
division of WEKA Publishing Inc., a privately held German
publisher of business reference products.
